# WEMS MCP Server — Documentation TOC
## Core MCP Server
- wems_mcp_server.py — Main MCP server with 11 natural hazard monitoring tools (3,245 lines)

## Natural Hazard Monitoring Tools
### Geological Hazards
- check_earthquakes — USGS earthquake monitoring with magnitude filtering and geographic bounds
- check_volcanoes — Smithsonian GVP + USGS volcanic activity alerts and eruption status
- check_tsunamis — NOAA PTWC + CTWC tsunami warnings across Pacific/Atlantic/Indian basins

### Weather & Climate Hazards  
- check_hurricanes — NHC tropical cyclone tracking with forecast tracks and intensity data
- check_severe_weather — NWS severe weather alerts (tornadoes, thunderstorms, flash floods)
- check_floods — USGS + NOAA flood warnings with river gauge data and flood stage monitoring
- check_wildfires — NWS + NIFC fire weather alerts and active fire perimeter data
- check_air_quality — OpenAQ global air quality monitoring (PM2.5, PM10, O₃, NO₂, SO₂, CO)
- check_drought_status — US Drought Monitor state drought conditions (D0-D4 levels, premium)

### Space Weather
- check_solar — NOAA SWPC space weather monitoring (K-index, solar flares, CMEs, geomagnetic storms)
- check_space_weather_alerts — Active space weather alerts and warnings from NOAA SWPC

### Security & Threats
- check_threat_advisories — DHS NTAS terrorism alerts, State Dept travel advisories, CISA cyber threats

## Configuration & Management
- configure_alerts — Alert threshold configuration and webhook endpoint management

